{
  "texts": [
    "The graph shows the effect of three defenses (hesitation reflector, safe reflector and prompt reflection) on reducing the success of IPI and FITD attacks across various models.",
    "may not be sufficient to counter complex attacks and may need to be combined with more robust defenses.",
    "In line with our earlier findings, we developed a hesitation reflection mechanism using an objective reflector based on LLaMA-3-1-70B.",
    "The reflector evaluates whether the agent's thought process shows hesitation or reluctance using a specific prompt (see directive H.2 in Appendix H).",
    "During testing on the 1000 benign thoughts, we observed no false positives to this reflector, confirming the mechanism's reliability in distinguishing safe requests."
  ]
}